gujarati.context:
Here are the translations:

The rich have remained in their pleasure, having passed the evening in joy; 
The seen and given to the servant, the known by the people as God.

Here is the translation:

Nearby were sages two, dead bodies; He was given a feast to eat;

After that, life-breath, became Brahma in the moment of God.

Here is the translation:

Worship done to the giver, then the servant is seen; 
then the image of Shrinaraayan is praised by seeing and worship.

Here is the translation:

People are many in Vas-Manhan, all have a wish to see God's sight; 
He does not get a home to go, only gets to see God's sight by death.

Ahoh nitye thataan darshan, ek hata eva pan dan;
Aja mookine chalya Mohan, hawa kyaare thasha darshan.

To English: Ah, daily one is seen, but still not understood; today in silence I went with Mohan, now when will the understanding come.

Here is the translation:

Gown worn thin, threadbare remaining known, from there Kundra got carried; 
After that Maharaaj came to Gharda, made this job absurd.
